    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Offered is a concours-level 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the legendary S54 3.2L inline-six power plant. This specimen showcases a high-revving 8,000 RPM redline facilitated by individual throttle bodies and a precision-tuned dual-VANOS variable valve timing system. The chassis integrity is superlative, featuring documented rear subframe reinforcement and a factory-spec M-Variable Lock limited-slip differential for optimal power delivery. The drivetrain is anchored by a Getrag 6-speed manual transmission with tight, short-throw gear synchronization. Suspension geometry remains true to factory specifications, utilizing its original MacPherson strut and multi-link configuration for telepathic handling. The exterior presents with flawless paint depth and zero curb rash on the forged 19-inch Style 67 wheels. Mechanically synchronized, free of fluid weeping, and stored in a climate-controlled environment, this is a museum-grade example for the discerning collector.",
